name: Cag-dev
tagline: A machine-corrected version of the Commentaria in Aristotelem Graeca.
body:
#Welcome to **cag-dev**!

##About
This repository hosts digital versions of the _Commentaria in Aristotelem Graeca_ (CAG).

These XML files were produced by data entry company [Digital Divide Data](http://www.digitaldividedata.org/) (DDD), who corrected and encoded hOCR output generated by [Bruce Robertson](https://github.com/brobertson) in accordance with the latest [EpiDoc](http://sourceforge.net/p/epidoc/wiki/Home/) standards.
While adequate, more can and should be done to improve the XML (the -dev(elopment) suffix indicates the repository is open to improvement).

A Wikipedia link to this repository can be viewed [here](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commentaria_in_Aristotelem_Graeca).

##Volumes

* [Vol. 1.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_1_1.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis metaphysica commentaria_ (1891) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 1.2](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_1_2.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis metaphysica commentaria_ (1891) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 2.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_2_1.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis analyticorum priorum librum 1 commentarium_ (1883) ed. Max Wallies.
* [Vol. 2.2] (https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_2_2.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis topicorum libros octo commentaria_ (1891) ed. Max Wallies.
* [Vol. 2.3](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_2_3.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _Quod fertur in Aristotelis sophisticos elenchos commentarium_ (1898) ed. Max Wallies.
* [Vol. 3.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_3_1.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In librum de sensu commentarium_ (1901) ed. Paul Wendland.
* [Vol. 3.2](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_3_2.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis metereologicorum libros commentarium_ (1899) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 4.2-6](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/master/commentaria_4_2.xml): Dexippus, _In Aristotelis Categorias commentarium_ (1888) ed. Adolf Busse.
* [Vol. 14.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_14_1.xml): Ioannis Philoponi, _In Aristotelis meteorologicorum librum primum commentarium_ (1901) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 17](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_17.xml): Ioannis Philoponi, _In Aristotelis physicorum libros tres priores commentaria_ (1887) ed. Geronimo Vitelli.
* [Vol. 19](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_19.xml): Aspasius, _In ethica Nicomachea quae supersunt commentaria_ (1889) ed. Gustav Heylbut; Heliodorus, _In ethica Nicomachea paraphrasis_ (1889) ed. Gustav Heylbut. 
* [Vol. 21.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_21_1.xml): Eustratius, _In analyticorum posteriorum librum secundum commentarium_ (1901) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 22.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_22_1.xml): Ephesius, _In parva naturalia commentaria_ (1903) ed. Paul Wendland.
* [Vol. 23](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_23.xml): Sophoniae, _In libros de anima paraphrasis_ (1883) ed. Michael Hayduck; Anonymi, _Categoriarum paraphrasis_ (1883) ed. Michael Hayduck; Themistii, _quae fertur in Aristotelis analyticorum priorum librum I paraphrasis_ (1884) ed. Max Wallies; Anonymi, _In sophisticos elenchos paraphrasis_ (1884) ed. Max Wallies.
